#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:15
msgid ""
"In version 2.0 of NvChad, the developers introduced the ability to create, "
"during the installation phase, a `custom` folder where you can make your own "
"customizations. The introduction of this feature allows you to have an "
"editor with the basic features of an IDE from the start."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:17
msgid ""
"The most important aspect of creating the _custom_ folder is writing the "
"files that contain the configurations for setting up some advanced features "
"such as language servers, linters, and formatters. These files allow us to "
"integrate, with just a few changes, the functionality we need."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:19
msgid ""
"The folder also contains files for code highlighting and custom command "
"mapping."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:21
msgid ""
"The folder is created from an example one on NvChad's GitHub repository: "
"([example-config](https://github.com/NvChad/example_config)). To create it "
"during the installation, simply answer \"y\" to the question we are asked at "
"the beginning of the installation:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:23
#, no-wrap
msgid ">  Do you want to install chadrc template? (y/N) :\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:25
msgid ""
"An affirmative answer will start a process that will clone the contents of "
"the _example-config_ folder from GitHub into **~/.config/nvim/lua/custom/** "
"and once finished, will remove the **.git** folder from it. This is to allow "
"us to put the configuration under our own version control."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:27
msgid "Upon completion we will have the following structure:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (text)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:28
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"custom/\n"
"칙춦춮칙춦칙춦 chadrc.lua\n"
"칙춦춮칙춦칙춦 init.lua\n"
"칙춦춮칙춦칙춦 plugins.lua\n"
"칙춦춮칙춦칙춦 mappings.lua\n"
"칙춦춮칙춦칙춦 highlights.lua\n"
"칙춦춮칙춦칙춦 configs\n"
"칙춦축츽먞 칙춦춮칙춦칙춦 lspconfig.lua\n"
"칙춦축츽먞 칙춦춮칙춦칙춦 null-ls.lua\n"
"칙춦축츽먞 칙춦춦칙춦칙춦 overrides.lua\n"
"칙춦춦칙춦칙춦 README.md\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:43
msgid ""
"As we can see, the folder contains some files with the same name also "
"encountered in the basic structure of NvChad. These files allow you to "
"integrate the configuration and override the basic settings of the editor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:44
#, no-wrap
msgid "Structure Analysis"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:47
msgid "Let us now go on to examine its contents:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:48
#, no-wrap
msgid "Main Files"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:50
#, no-wrap
msgid "chadrc.lua"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:52
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"---@type ChadrcConfig\n"
"local M = {}\n"
"\n"
"-- Path to overriding theme and highlights files\n"
"local highlights = require \"custom.highlights\"\n"
"\n"
"M.ui = {\n"
"  theme = \"onedark\",\n"
"  theme_toggle = { \"onedark\", \"one_light\" },\n"
"\n"
"  hl_override = highlights.override,\n"
"  hl_add = highlights.add,\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"M.plugins = \"custom.plugins\"\n"
"\n"
"-- check core.mappings for table structure\n"
"M.mappings = require \"custom.mappings\"\n"
"\n"
"return M\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:76
msgid ""
"The file is inserted into the Neovim configuration by the `load_config` "
"function set in the file **~/.config/nvim/lua/core/utils.lua**, a function "
"that takes care of loading the default settings and, if present, also those "
"of our _chadrc.lua_:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:77
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"M.load_config = function()\n"
"  local config = require \"core.default_config\"\n"
"  local chadrc_path = vim.api.nvim_get_runtime_file(\"lua/custom/chadrc.lua\", false)[1]\n"
"...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:85
msgid ""
"Its function is to insert files from our _custom_ folder into the NvChad "
"configuration to then be used along with the default files to start the "
"_Neovim_ instance. The files are inserted into the configuration tree "
"through `require` functions such as:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:86
#, no-wrap
msgid "require \"custom.mappings\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:91
msgid ""
"The string **custom.mappings** indicates the relative path to the file "
"without the extension as opposed to the default path, which in this case is "
"**~/.config/nvim/lua/**. The dot replaces the slash since this is the "
"convention in code written in Lua (in the _lua language_ there is no concept "
"of _directory_)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:93
msgid ""
"In summary, we can say that the call described above inserts the "
"configurations written in the **custom/mappings.lua** file into the NvChad "
"mapping thus inserting our shortcuts to invoke the commands of our plugins."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:95
msgid ""
"We then have a section that overrides some of the NvChad UI configuration "
"settings contained in **~/.config/nvim/lua/core/default_config.lua**, more "
"specifically the `M.ui` section that allows us, for example, to select a "
"light or dark theme."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:97
msgid ""
"And we also have the inclusion of our plugins defined in **custom/plugins."
"lua** corresponding to the string:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "M.plugins = \"custom.plugins\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:103
msgid ""
"In this way our plugins will be passed along with those that make up the "
"NvChad configuration to _lazy.nvim_ for installation and management. The "
"inclusion in this case is not in the Neovim tree but rather in the "
"configuration of _lazy.nvim_ since this plugin completely disables the "
"relative functionality of the editor with the call `vim.go.loadplugins = "
"false`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:104
#, no-wrap
msgid "init.lua"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:107
msgid ""
"This file is used for overwriting settings defined in **~/.config/nvim/lua/"
"core/init.lua**, such as indentation or swap write interval, to disk. It is "
"also used for the creation of auto-commands, as described in the commented "
"lines in the file. An example might be the following in which some settings "
"for writing documents in Markdown have been included:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:108
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"--local autocmd = vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd\n"
"\n"
"-- settings for Markdown\n"
"local opt = vim.opt\n"
"\n"
"opt.tabstop = 4\n"
"opt.softtabstop = 4\n"
"opt.shiftwidth = 4\n"
"opt.shiftround = false\n"
"opt.expandtab = true\n"
"opt.autoindent = true\n"
"opt.smartindent = true\n"
"\n"
"-- Auto resize panes when resizing nvim window\n"
"--autocmd(\"VimResized\", {\n"
"--   pattern = \"*\",\n"
"--   command = \"tabdo wincmd =\",\n"
"-- })\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:130
msgid "In this way our settings will replace the default settings."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:131
#, no-wrap
msgid "plugins.lua"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:134
msgid ""
"This file, as you can guess from the name, is used to add our plugins to "
"those in the basic NvChad configuration. The insertion of plugins is "
"explained in detail on the page dedicated to [Plugins Manager](nvchad_ui/"
"plugins_manager.md)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:136
msgid ""
"The _plugins.lua_ file created by the _template chadrc_ has in the first "
"part a number of customizations that override the plugin definition options "
"and default plugin configurations. This part of the file does not need to be "
"modified by us as the developers have prepared special files for this "
"purpose that are present in the _config_ folder."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:138
msgid ""
"Then follows the installation of a plugin. This is set up as an example so "
"that you can begin to become familiar with the format used by _lazy.nvim_ "
"which differs slightly from the format used by _packer.nvim_, the handler "
"used in version 1.0."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:139
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  -- Install a plugin\n"
"  {\n"
"    \"max397574/better-escape.nvim\",\n"
"    event = \"InsertEnter\",\n"
"    config = function()\n"
"      require(\"better_escape\").setup()\n"
"    end,\n"
"  },\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:151
msgid ""
"After this plugin and before the last bracket we can insert all our plugins. "
"There is a whole ecosystem of plugins suitable for every purpose. For an "
"initial overview you can visit [Neovimcraft](https://neovimcraft.com/)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:152
#, no-wrap
msgid "mappings.lua"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:155
msgid ""
"This file inserts into the configuration tree the mappings (keyboard "
"shortcuts) that will be needed to invoke the commands of the plugins we are "
"going to add."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:157
msgid ""
"An example setting is also presented here so that its format can be studied:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:158
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"M.general = {\n"
"  n = {\n"
"    [\";\"] = { \":\", \"enter command mode\", opts = { nowait = true } },\n"
"  },\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:167
#, no-wrap
msgid "This mapping is entered for the NORMAL state `n =` the character <kbd>;</kbd> which when pressed on the keyboard plays the character <kbd>:</kbd>. This character is the character used to enter COMMAND mode. The option `nowait = true` is also set to enter that mode immediately. In this way on a keyboard with a US QWERTY layout, we will not need to use <kbd>SHIFT</kbd> to enter COMMAND mode.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:169
msgid "!!! Tip"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:171
#, no-wrap
msgid "    For users of European keyboards (such as Italian), it is recommended to substitute the character <kbd>;</kbd> with <kbd>,</kbd>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:172
#, no-wrap
msgid "highlights.lua"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:175
msgid ""
"The file is used to customize the style of the editor. The settings written "
"here are used to change aspects such as font style (**bold**,_italic_), "
"background color of an element, foreground color, etc.."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:176
#, no-wrap
msgid "Configs folder"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:179
msgid ""
"The files in this folder are all configuration files that are used in the "
"**custom/plugins.lua** file to change the default settings of the plugins "
"that deal with language servers (_lspconfig_), linter/formatters (_null-"
"ls_), and for overriding the basic settings of **treesitter**, **mason**, "
"and **nvim-tree** (_override_)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (text)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:180
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"configs/\n"
"칙춦춮칙춦칙춦 lspconfig.lua\n"
"칙춦춮칙춦칙춦 null-ls.lua\n"
"칙춦춦칙춦칙춦 overrides.lua\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:187
#, no-wrap
msgid "lspconfig.lua"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:190
msgid ""
"The _lspconfig.lua_ file sets the local language servers that the editor can "
"use. This will allow for advanced features for supported files, such as "
"autocomplete or snippets, for quick creation of pieces of code. To add our "
"_lsp_ to the configuration, we simply edit the table (in _lua_ what is "
"represented below in curly brackets is a table) prepared especially by the "
"NvChad developers:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:191
#, no-wrap
msgid "local servers = { \"html\", \"cssls\", \"tsserver\", \"clangd\" }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:196
msgid ""
"As we can see some servers are already set up by default. To add a new one "
"simply enter it at the end of the table. The available servers can be found "
"at [mason packages](https://github.com/williamboman/mason.nvim/blob/main/"
"PACKAGES.md) and for their configurations you can refer to [lsp server "
"configurations](https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/blob/master/doc/"
"server_configurations.md)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:198
msgid ""
"For example if we also want to have support for the `yaml` language we can "
"add it as in the following example:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:199
#, no-wrap
msgid "local servers = { \"html\", \"cssls\", \"tsserver\", \"clangd\", \"yamlls\" }\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:204
msgid ""
"Changing the file, however, does not involve installing the related language "
"server. This will have to be installed separately with _Mason_. The language "
"server that provides support for _yaml_ is [yaml-language-server](https://"
"github.com/redhat-developer/yaml-language-server) which we will have to "
"install with the command `:MasonInstall yaml-language-server`. At this point "
"we will have, for example, control of the code written in the headers "
"(_frontmatter_) of the Rocky Linux documentation pages."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:205
#, no-wrap
msgid "null-ls.lua"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:208
msgid ""
"This file takes care of configuring some features geared toward control and "
"formatting of written code. Editing this file requires a bit more research "
"for configuration than the previous file. An overview of the available "
"components can be found on [the builtins page](https://github.com/jose-elias-"
"alvarez/null-ls.nvim/blob/main/doc/BUILTINS.md)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:210
msgid ""
"Again, a table has been set up, the `local sources` table, where we can "
"enter our customizations which we can see below:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:211
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"local sources = {\n"
"\n"
"  -- webdev stuff\n"
"  b.formatting.deno_fmt,\n"
"  b.formatting.prettier.with { filetypes = { \"html\", \"markdown\", \"css\" } },\n"
"  -- Lua\n"
"  b.formatting.stylua,\n"
"\n"
"  -- cpp\n"
"  b.formatting.clang_format,\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:226
msgid ""
"As we can see, in the initial configuration only formatters were included, "
"but we might for example need a diagnostic for the Markdown language and in "
"that case we could add [Markdownlint](https://github.com/DavidAnson/"
"markdownlint) like this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:227
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  -- diagnostic markdown\n"
"  b.diagnostics.markdownlint,\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:233
msgid ""
"Again, the configuration needs the installation of the related package, "
"which we are going to install always with _Mason_:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (text)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:234
#, no-wrap
msgid ":MasonInstall markdownlint\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:239
msgid "!!! Note"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:241
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Configuration of this diagnostic tool also requires the creation of a configuration file in your home folder, which will not be covered in this document.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ####
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:242
#, no-wrap
msgid "overrides.lua"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:245
msgid ""
"The _overrides.lua_ file contains the changes to be made to the default "
"plugin settings. The plugins to which the changes are to be applied are "
"specified in the `-- override plugin configs` section of the **custom/"
"plugins.lua** file through the use of the `opts` option (e.g. `opts = "
"overrides.mason`)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:247
msgid ""
"In the initial configuration there are three plugins marked as needing to be "
"overridden and they are _treesitter_, _mason_ and _nvim-tree_. Leaving out "
"_nvim-tree_ for the moment, we will focus on the first two that allow us to "
"change our editing experience significantly."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:249
msgid ""
"_treesitter_ is a code parser that takes care of its formatting in an "
"interactive way. Whenever we save a file recognized by _treesitter_ it is "
"passed to the parser which returns an optimally indented and highlighted "
"code tree, so it will be easier to read, interpret and edit the code in the "
"editor."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:251
msgid "The part of the code that deals with this is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:252
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"M.treesitter = {\n"
"  ensure_installed = {\n"
"    \"vim\",\n"
"    \"lua\",\n"
"    \"html\",\n"
"    \"css\",\n"
"    \"javascript\",\n"
"    \"typescript\",\n"
"    \"tsx\",\n"
"    \"c\",\n"
"    \"markdown\",\n"
"    \"markdown_inline\",\n"
"  },\n"
"  indent = {\n"
"    enable = true,\n"
"    -- disable = {\n"
"    --   \"python\"\n"
"    -- },\n"
"  },\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:276
msgid ""
"Now following the example given earlier, if we want the _frontmatter_ of our "
"documentation pages on Rocky Linux to be highlighted correctly we can add "
"support for _yaml_ in the `ensure_installed` table after the last parser set:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (text)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:277
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ...\n"
"    \"tsx\",\n"
"    \"c\",\n"
"    \"markdown\",\n"
"    \"markdown_inline\",\n"
"    \"yaml\",\n"
"    ...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:288
msgid ""
"Now the next time we open NvChad, the parser we just added will also be "
"automatically installed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:290
msgid ""
"To have the parser available directly in the running instance of NvChad we "
"can always install it, even without having edited the file, with the command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (text)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:291
#, no-wrap
msgid ":TSInstall yaml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:296
msgid ""
"Following in the file is the part regarding the installation of servers by "
"_Mason_. All servers set in this table are installed in one operation with "
"the command `:MasonInstallAll` (this command is also invoked during the "
"creation of the _custom_ folder). The part is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:297
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"M.mason = {\n"
"  ensure_installed = {\n"
"    -- lua stuff\n"
"    \"lua-language-server\",\n"
"    \"stylua\",\n"
"\n"
"    -- web dev stuff\n"
"    \"css-lsp\",\n"
"    \"html-lsp\",\n"
"    \"typescript-language-server\",\n"
"    \"deno\",\n"
"    \"prettier\"\n"
"  },\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:315
msgid ""
"Again, following the initial example where we enabled support for _yaml_ by "
"manually installing the server, we can make sure we always have it installed "
"by adding it to the table:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (text)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:316
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ...\n"
"    \"typescript-language-server\",\n"
"    \"deno\",\n"
"    \"prettier\",\n"
"\n"
"    -- yaml-language-server\n"
"    \"yaml-language-server\",\n"
"    ...\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:328
msgid ""
"Although this aspect may be marginal on a running instance of NvChad since "
"we can always manually install the missing servers it turns out to be very "
"useful during the transfer of our configuration from one machine to another."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:330
msgid ""
"For example, suppose we have configured our `custom` folder with all the "
"features we need and we want to transfer it to another installation of "
"NvChad. If we have configured this file, after copying or cloning our "
"`custom` folder a `:MasonInstallAll` will be sufficient to have all the "
"servers ready to use on the other installation as well."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:332
msgid ""
"The final part of the configuration, the `M.nvimtree` section, takes care of "
"configuring _nvim-tree_ by enabling the functionality to display the state "
"in the file tree with respect to the git repository:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:333
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  git = {\n"
"    enable = true,\n"
"  },\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:340
msgid "their highlighting and corresponding icons:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/template_chadrc.md:341
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  renderer = {\n"
"    highlight_git = true,\n"
"    icons = {\n"
"      show = {\n"
"        git = true,\n"
"      },\n"
"    },\n"
"  },\n"
msgstr ""

